data.title: What is the definition of Zizyphus?
data.meta_description: Zizyphus - A genus of shruba or trees of the Rhamneae; in the pi., zizyphi, the fruits of Z. vulgaris. Z. A in ...
data.text:
ziz'i-fus, n. a genus of shrubs or trees of the buckthorn family, mostly native to tropical Asia and America--the jujube-tree. [L.,--Gr. zizyphos.]

1908 - Chambers's Twentieth Century Dictionary of the English Language

By Thomas Davidson
